To live well means to be happy.
If you’re looking for happiness, I suggest that a little bit of the ‘old school’ philosophy may serve as an excellent guide. The word happiness is often used in two different ways – it can refer both to our present state and also what we hope will become ours at some point down the line (i.e., being contented).
Now, before anyone gets too excited about this idea: If there’s one thing many people are not good with they tend towards discontentment;
